Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportCritNet(25.10)                                      reportCritNet(25.10)

Name
       reportCritNet  -  Generates a file containing a list of nets which have
       critical slack for the  currently  specified  (setup  or  hold)  timing
       analysis mode

Syntax
       reportCritNet

       [-help]

       [-nrCritNets <integer>]

       [-outfile <fileName>]

       [-targetSlack <double>]

       [-view <viewName>]

       Generates  a  file  containing a list of nets which have critical slack
       for the currently specified (setup or hold) timing analysis mode.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each reportCritNet parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man reportCritNet

       -nrCritNets <integer>
              Restricts the number of critical nets reported to the first <in-
              teger> most critical nets.

       -outfile <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the report file.

       -targetSlack <double>
              Reports nets with slack less than the specified slack value.

       -view <viewName>
              Generates the report based on the specified analysis view  only.
              You  can  specify  this  parameter  only when the software is in
              multi-mode multi-corner timing analysis mode.

Command Order
       Use this command after the timing graph is built.

Example
       The following command generates a report named critnet that lists crit-
       ical nets:

       reportCritNet -outfile critnet

